      'caption': '''Command-line parameters for the alternative browser.''',
      'tags': [],
      'desc': '''Setting the policy to a list of strings means each string is passed to the alternative browser as separate command-line parameters. On <ph name="MS_WIN_NAME">Microsoft速 Windows速</ph>, the parameters are joined with spaces. On <ph name="MAC_OS_NAME">macOS</ph> and <ph name="LINUX_OS_NAME">Linux速</ph>, a parameter can have spaces and still be treated as a single parameter.

      If an parameter contains <ph name="URL_PLACEHOLDER">${url}</ph>, <ph name="URL_PLACEHOLDER">${url}</ph> is replaced with the URL of the page to open. If no parameter contains <ph name="URL_PLACEHOLDER">${url}</ph>, the URL is appended at the end of the command line.

